Clustering Analysis Libraries

There are many libraries and functions in R for performing clustering analysis, so why look at these 2? Well, they solve two important challenges with clustering: visualisation and determining the optimal number of clusters.

In general, cluster analysis is an unsupervised machine learning task, meaning we dont predefine a target output for the learning. For clustering, this mainly means that we dont know what the categories will be before we start the analysis. We also dont know how many clusters are present.
